[size=150][b]Limitations[/b][/size]
All resizing options will convert the image into a PNG image no matter the original image's format. This wouldn't be a problem, until you try to resize an animated GIF and end up with a PNG file without animation. This is a limitation of the HTML canvases. Nothing can be done about this, other than resize the image with an image editor software (GIMP, Photoshop, etc.) and then load it into the browser to convert it to Base64.
[u]The item [b]Convert to Base64[/b] on the context menu is not affected by this. It will respect the original image's MIME type.[/u]

